{\"Name\", .Name, \"InstanceId\", .InstanceId}' This command uses the AWS CLI to describe EC2 instances, and then pipes the output to `jq` to format the output in a JSON-like format, showing the instance name and ID.\n\n### Development\n\n    \n    \n    pip install --user pipenv pipenv --python 3.11 pipenv install\n\n### TODO\n\n  * Fix the setup and pyproject file, including github workflow for releasing the package\n\n## About\n\nLFG, It Really Whips the Llama's Ass \ud83e\udd99\ud83e\udd99\ud83e\udd99\ud83e\udd99\n\n### Resources\n\nReadme\n\nActivity\n\n### Stars\n\n4 stars\n\n### Watchers\n\n2 watching\n\n### Forks\n\n0 forks\n\nReport repository\n\n## Releases\n\nNo releases published\n\n## Packages 0\n\nNo packages published\n\n## Languages\n\n  * Python 94.2%\n  * Shell 5.8%\n\n## Footer\n\n\u00a9 2024 GitHub, Inc.\n\nYou can\u2019t perform that action at this time.\n\n", "frontpage": false}
